    & You must make your way through a seemingly endless succession of rooms. You will not be alone. Your incarnations will have the help of {(bold "bizaroid")} characters that speak an {(link "Camilare" "an obscure language")}.
    & We made Oquonie while living in {(link "Japan")}. The game was our first collaborative project as {(link "Hundred Rabbits")}, and a reflection of our experience navigating a new country, with language as a recurent obstacle. Oquonie is about being lost in a foreign space.
