  BODY
    & The {(bold "Raspberry Pi")} is a small inexpensive single-board computer.
    & To get started with a new device, download {(link "https://www.raspberrypi.org/downloads/raspbian/" "Raspbian Lite")}, and use {(link "https://etcher.io" "Etcher")} to flash the SD card.
    * SSH
    & You can use {(code "ssh")} to input commands and {(bold "remotely control the device")}, follow these steps to get started.
    # touch /Volumes/boot/ssh <comment># Enable SSH</comment>
    # touch /Volumes/boot/wpa_supplicant.conf <comment># Auto-connect to wifi</comment>
    * Setup Wifi
    & Input your wireless network details to enable the device to {(bold "automatically connect to the network")} when available.
    # <comment># nano /Volumes/boot/wpa_supplicant.conf</comment>
    # country=CA
    # ctrl_interface=DIR=/var/run/wpa_supplicant GROUP=netdev
    # update_config=1
    # network={
    #   ssid="network_name"
    #   psk="network_password"
    # }
    * Connect
    & When {(code "ssh")} has been activated and the wifi details updated, the device should become discoverable.
    # ping raspberrypi.local <comment># Find its IP address</comment>
    # ssh pi@192.168.1.73 <comment># Use password "{(bold "raspberry")}"</comment>
    # sudo raspi-config <comment># {(bold "Interface/SSH")} & {(bold "Advanced/Expand FS")}</comment>
    # sudo nano /etc/hostname <comment># Rename</comment>
    # sudo nano /etc/hosts <comment># Rename</comment>
    # passwd <comment># Change Password</comment>
    # sudo reboot
    * Gadget Mode
    & Gadget mode allows to {(bold "SSH")} into a {(link "Raspberry" "Raspberry Pi Zero")} device via USB. Begin by {(bold "enabling ssh")}, by adding {(code "/Volumes/boot/ssh")} to the SD Card. Activate {(bold "gadget mode")} , allowing the device to be discovered and controlled via USB.
    # dtoverlay=dwc2 <comment># Append to config.txt</comment>
    # modules-load=dwc2,g_ether <comment># Append to cmdline.txt, or after rootwait</comment>
    * Basics
    & Make sure everything is up-to-date and install {(code "git")}.
    # sudo apt-get update
    # sudo apt-get dist-upgrade
    # sudo apt-get install git
    λ (template host:children "full")
