DONSOL
  UNDE : Games
  BREF : {(link)} is a {(bold "dungeon-crawler card game")}.
  ICON : M150,60 l-90,90 l90,90 l90,-90 l-90,-90
  BODY
    & {(bold "Donsol")}, designed by {(link "https://twitter.com/johneternal" "John Eternal")}, is a card game about exploring a dungeon of 54 playing cards.
    & {(bold "A standard deck of 54 cards")}, jokers included, is a dungeon. Shuffle the deck and draw 4 cards, display them before you, this is a room. A room ends when all the cards are folded.
    % itchio 109936
    * ♥︎ Heart Potions
    & A {(bold "potion")} gives you health points equal to its value, up to a maximum of 21 health points.
    & Drinking multiple potions in a row will make you sick and result in no extra healing, only the first potion's value will be gained in HP. Potions are equal to their value and face cards (J,Q,K,A) each are equal to 11.
    * ♦ Diamond Shields
    & A {(bold "shield")} absorbs the damage difference between the shield value and that of the attacked monster's value.
    & Shields can only defend against monsters in descending value and if you use a shield on a monster with higher or equal value to the previous, it will break. Broken shields leave you unarmored, and taking full damage. Folding shield card will always replace a previously equipped shield. Shields are equal to their value and face cards (J,Q,K,A) each are equal to 11.
    * ♣♠ Club/Spades Monsters
    & Monster cards are equal to their value, and face cards are as follows J is 11, Q is 13, K is 15, A is 17; Jokers are both equal to 21.
    & You may {(bold "escape a room")}. When escaping, the remaining cards are shuffled back into the deck. A player is allowed to escape a room when:
    - All monsters have been dealt with. ({(bold "Easy Mode")})
    - And, the player has not escaped the previous room. ({(bold "Normal Mode")})
    - And, there is only one card left in the room. ({(bold "Hard Mode")})
    - Can never escape. ({(bold "Expert Mode")})
    % youtube GNoZrr56GqA
    ? The game was created in collaboration with {(link "https://twitter.com/johneternal" "John Eternal")}, released for {(link "Mobile")} back in 2016, and re-released for Desktop in 2017 as {(link "Hundred Rabbits")}. While the game was designed on a train, without internet connection, it seemed like Donsol's gameplay accidentally ended up being a twist to Zach Gage and Kurt Bieg's {(link "http://stfj.net/index2.php?project=art/2011/Scoundrel.pdf" "Scoundrel")}, designed in 2011.
  LINK
    Itch : https://hundredrabbits.itch.io/donsol
    Sources : https://github.com/hundredrabbits/Donsol
