    & {(bold "Nohlxeserre")} is a language that delivers a richer and more precise rendition of its meaning than actual experience.
    & The richness and detail of experiencing an event, pales in comparison to having it recited – Effictively inducing the symptoms of {(link "Neausea")}, stasis, and ultimately death.
    & The Nohlxeserre Language is the language of the {(link "Actors")}. Andes, as opposed to {(link "Neonev")}, did not found itself on {(link "Dinaisth")} looking for {(link "Actors")}, but for {(link "Paradichlorisse")}. Whom Andes says "{(ital "Speaks the language of the birds")}".
    @ When {(link "Paradichlorisse")} spoke of silence, silence fell.
