    & Below are the organized and templated notes from my {(link "Russian")} studies.
    & They might serve you as a good basis to get into the language. This series of notes is inspired from Tad Perry's 1992 {(ital "Quick and Dirty Guide to Japanese")}.
    & {(bold "The nominative")} is the basic(dictionary) form of the noun when removed from context.
    # {(bold "Студентка")} задала вопрос <comment>The student asked a question.</comment>
    & {(bold "The accusative")} is the goal of the action, or the target of the verb.
    # Учитель открыл {(bold "окно")} <comment>The teacher opened the window.</comment>
    & {(bold "The genitive")} is used to express a relationship between two nouns.
    # Это портофель {(bold "профессора")} <comment>This is the professor's briefcase.</comment>
    & {(bold "The dative")} is used when the noun is the recipient of an action.
    # Маша даёт билет {(bold "борису")} <comment>Masha is giving the ticket to Boris.</comment>
    & {(bold "The instrumental")} is used when the noun is the instrument or mean by which an action is performed.
    # Ученик пишет {(bold "карандашом")} <comment>The student writes with a pencil.</comment>
    & The gender of the noun determines the gender of the pronoun.
    | Where is my table  | Где мо{(bold "й")} сто{(bold "л")}
    | Where is my window | Где мо{(bold "ё")} окн{(bold "о")}
    | Where is my lamp   | Где мо{(bold "я")} ламп{(bold "а")}
    & The gender of the noun determines the gender of the adjective.
    | This is a new table |  Это новы{(bold "й")} сто{(bold "л")}
    | This is a new window |  Это ново{(bold "е")} окн{(bold "о")}
    | This is a new lamp |  Это нова{(bold "я")} ламп{(bold "а")}
    & The gender of the noun determines the predicate verb.
    | The table was there |  Сто{(bold "л")} бы{(bold "л")} там
    | The window was there |  Окн{(bold "о")} был{(bold "о")} там
    | The lamp was there |  Ламп{(bold "а")} был{(bold "а")} там
    & It's amazing how many sentences can be made with knowing these simple 3 words: нет, был & будет.
    | The student is at home.      |  Студент дома.
    | The student is not at home.  |  Студента {(bold "нет")} дома.
    | The student was home.        |  Студент {(bold "был")} дома.
    | The student will be home.    |  Студент {(bold "будет")} дома.
    & Conjugation Table
    | {(bold "Present")}          |                | {(bold "Past")}         |                      | {(bold "Future")}
    | It is cold           | холодно        | It was cold      | было холодно         | It will be cold      | будет холодно
    | It is not cold       | не холодно     | It was not cold  | не было холодно      | It will not be cold  | не быдет холодно
    | I am cold            | мне холодно    | I was cold       | мне было холодно     | I shall be cold      | мне будет холодно
    | We are cold          | нам холодно    | We were cold     | нам было холодно     | We shall be cold     | нам быдет холодно
    | You are cold         | тебе холодно   | You were cold    | тебе было холодно    | You shall be cold    | тебе будет холодно
    | Yous are cold        | вам холодно    | Yous were cold   | вам было холодно     | Yous shall be cold   | вам быдет холодно
    | He/She is cold       | ему/ей холодно | He/She was cold  | ему/ей было холодно  | He/She shall be cold | ему/ей будет холодно
    | They are cold        | им холодно     | They were cold   | им было холодно      | They shall be cold   | им быдет холодно
